00:00:11.053 --> 00:00:12.720
SCOTT HUGHES: All
right, good afternoon.

00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:18.540
So today's lecture is a
particularly important one.

00:00:18.540 --> 00:00:22.890
We are going to introduce the
main physical principle that

00:00:22.890 --> 00:00:25.680
underlies general relativity.

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:28.320
We'll be spending a bunch of
time connecting that principle

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:31.050
to the mathematics as the
rest of the term unwinds.

00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:33.210
But today is where we're
going to really lay out

00:00:33.210 --> 00:00:35.400
where the physics
is in what is known

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:37.230
as the principle of equivalence.

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:39.360
So before I get into
that, just a quick recap.

00:00:39.360 --> 00:00:42.700
So in terms of technical
stuff we did last time,

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:44.700
the most important
thing we did was

00:00:44.700 --> 00:00:46.830
to introduce these
mathematical objects called

00:00:46.830 --> 00:00:48.750
Christoffel symbols.

00:00:48.750 --> 00:00:52.590
Christoffel symbols are
those capital gammas.

00:00:52.590 --> 00:00:54.660
We began by thinking
of them as just what

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:56.940
you get when you look at
the derivative of your basis

00:00:56.940 --> 00:00:58.920
objects.

00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:00.578
Pardon me a second.

00:01:00.578 --> 00:01:02.370
There was a lot of
chalk on the chalkboard,

00:01:02.370 --> 00:01:06.330
and I think I inhaled half of
it while I was cleaning it.

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:08.160
So take derivatives
of your basis vectors.

00:01:08.160 --> 00:01:11.520
And there, you get something
that's linearly related

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:12.690
to your basis objects.

00:01:12.690 --> 00:01:17.190
And the gamma is the set
of mathematical quantities

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:18.900
that sets that
linear relationship

00:01:18.900 --> 00:01:22.860
between the derivatives
and the objects themselves.

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:25.320
One can build under the demand--

00:01:25.320 --> 00:01:27.150
so recall how we did this.

00:01:27.150 --> 00:01:29.340
We have a physical
argument that tells us

00:01:29.340 --> 00:01:32.880
that a quantity we call the
covariant derivative, which

00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:36.300
is a way of using these
Christoffel symbols in order

00:01:36.300 --> 00:01:38.560
to get tensorial derivatives.

00:01:38.560 --> 00:01:42.630
So if I look at just the
partial derivative of a tensor,

00:01:42.630 --> 00:01:45.900
if I'm working in a general
curvilinear coordinate system,

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:47.730
the set of partial
derivatives do not

00:01:47.730 --> 00:01:50.200
constitute components
of a tensor.

00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:50.700
OK?

00:01:50.700 --> 00:01:55.020
I posted some notes online,
demonstrating explicitly

00:01:55.020 --> 00:01:56.400
why that is.

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:57.960
But in a nutshell,
the main reason

00:01:57.960 --> 00:02:00.730
is that, when you
try to work this out

00:02:00.730 --> 00:02:02.733
or when you go and
you work this out,

00:02:02.733 --> 00:02:04.650
you will find that there
are additional terms.

00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:07.710
It was like the derivative of
the transformation matrix that

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:10.110
come in and spoil
the tensoriality

00:02:10.110 --> 00:02:11.568
of this relationship.

00:02:11.568 --> 00:02:13.110
And what the
Christoffel symbol does,

00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:15.200
as you guys are going
to prove on P set three,

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:17.580
it introduces terms
that are exactly

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:19.470
the same but with
the opposite sign

00:02:19.470 --> 00:02:21.160
and cancel those things out.

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:23.700
So that the covariant
derivative is

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:25.740
what I get when I
correct each index

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:28.110
with an appropriate factor
of the Christoffel symbol.

00:02:28.110 --> 00:02:31.540
It is something that is
a component of a tensor.

00:02:31.540 --> 00:02:33.750
In other words, it obeys
the transformation laws

00:02:33.750 --> 00:02:36.480
that tensors must have.

00:02:36.480 --> 00:02:38.790
We have a physical
argument that essentially

00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:42.330
is something that is
tensorial, in other words, both

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:45.960
sides of the equations are
good tensor quantities in one

00:02:45.960 --> 00:02:48.210
representation,
have to be tensorial

00:02:48.210 --> 00:02:50.010
in any other representation.

00:02:50.010 --> 00:02:52.440
And from that, we deduced
that the covariant derivative

00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:55.080
of the metric must always be 0.

00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:57.160
And by taking appropriate
covariant derivatives

00:02:57.160 --> 00:03:00.030
of the metric, sort of doing a
bit of gymnastics with indices

00:03:00.030 --> 00:03:02.320
and sort of wiggling
things around a little bit,

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:04.350
we found that the
Christoffel symbol can itself

00:03:04.350 --> 00:03:08.130
be built out of partial
derivatives of the metric.

00:03:08.130 --> 00:03:10.710
And the result looks like this.

00:03:10.710 --> 00:03:14.070
So that's a little bit
more of an in-depth recap

00:03:14.070 --> 00:03:15.917
than I typically do.

00:03:15.917 --> 00:03:18.000
But I really want to hammer
that home because this

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.690
is an important point.

00:03:19.690 --> 00:03:20.967
We then began switching gears.

00:03:20.967 --> 00:03:22.300
And we're going to do something.

00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:27.030
So I introduced, at the end of
the previous lecture, a fairly

00:03:27.030 --> 00:03:29.970
silly argument,
which, nonetheless,

00:03:29.970 --> 00:03:33.550
has an important
physical concept to it.

00:03:33.550 --> 00:03:36.630
So where we were going
with was the fact that,

00:03:36.630 --> 00:03:57.660
when we have gravity, we cannot
cover all of spacetime with

00:03:57.660 --> 00:04:02.950
inertial frames,
or I should say--

00:04:02.950 --> 00:04:04.520
I should watch my wording here--

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:07.620
with an inertial frame.

00:04:07.620 --> 00:04:08.120
OK?

00:04:08.120 --> 00:04:09.200
We're, in fact,
going to see that you

00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:10.820
can have a sequence of them.

00:04:10.820 --> 00:04:13.050
And we're going to find
ways of linking them up.

00:04:13.050 --> 00:04:15.260
But for now, if you think
of special relativity

00:04:15.260 --> 00:04:17.180
as the theory of
physics in which we

00:04:17.180 --> 00:04:20.360
can have Lorentz coordinates
that cover the entire universe,

00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:22.140
that's out the window.

00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:24.650
OK, and so I'm going to
skip my silly derivation.

00:04:24.650 --> 00:04:27.650
Part one of it is
essentially just a motivation

00:04:27.650 --> 00:04:29.765
that a gravitational
redshift exists.

00:04:38.170 --> 00:04:39.910
So I gave a silly
little demonstration

00:04:39.910 --> 00:04:42.550
where you imagined dropping
a rock off of a tower.

00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:44.800
You had some kind of a magical
device that converts it

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:46.390
into a photon that
shoots it back up

00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:48.460
and then converts
it back into a rock.

00:04:48.460 --> 00:04:50.360
And you showed that,
as it climbed out

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:52.390
of the gravitational
potential, it

00:04:52.390 --> 00:04:54.295
had to lose some of its energy.

00:04:54.295 --> 00:04:56.170
Or else, you would get
more energy at the top

00:04:56.170 --> 00:04:58.087
than you put in when you
initially dropped it.

00:04:58.087 --> 00:05:00.580
It's a way of preventing you
from making perpetual motion

00:05:00.580 --> 00:05:02.298
machines.

00:05:02.298 --> 00:05:04.090
That is, without a
doubt, a flaky argument.

00:05:04.090 --> 00:05:05.840
It can be made a little
bit more rigorous.

00:05:05.840 --> 00:05:08.380
But I didn't want to.

00:05:08.380 --> 00:05:11.860
And I will justify the reason
I can do this is that this is,

00:05:11.860 --> 00:05:17.430
in fact, a highly tested
experimental fact.

00:05:23.520 --> 00:05:25.020
Every single one
of you has probably

00:05:25.020 --> 00:05:27.450
used this if you've
ever used GPS

00:05:27.450 --> 00:05:29.070
to find your way
to some location

00:05:29.070 --> 00:05:31.390
where you're supposed
to meet a friend.

00:05:31.390 --> 00:05:34.800
And what this basically
tells me is that,

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:40.040
if I imagine a
tower of height h,

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:45.290
if I shoot light with
frequency at the bottom, omega

00:05:45.290 --> 00:05:49.720
b, when it reaches
the top, it'll

00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:52.020
have a different
frequency, omega t,

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:55.270
where these are
related by omega t

00:05:55.270 --> 00:06:01.300
equals, and I'm going to put my
c squareds back in there, just

00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:03.410
to keep it all complete.

00:06:03.410 --> 00:06:03.910
OK?

00:06:03.910 --> 00:06:09.610
So this is, I emphasize,
a very precisely

00:06:09.610 --> 00:06:12.280
calibrated experimental
result. There

00:06:12.280 --> 00:06:15.050
are many ways of doing it,
some silly, some serious.

00:06:15.050 --> 00:06:16.300
The silly one was sort of fun.

00:06:16.300 --> 00:06:18.600
But it does actually capture
the experimental fact.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:19.100
OK?

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:22.450
The key experimental fact is
that it's necessary for light

00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:25.690
to lose energy as it climbs
out of the gravitational field,

00:06:25.690 --> 00:06:29.170
in essence, because it's
possible, thanks to quantum

00:06:29.170 --> 00:06:32.230
field theory, to convert photons
into particles and particles

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:33.040
into photons.

00:06:33.040 --> 00:06:36.070
This is a way of
conserving energy.

00:06:36.070 --> 00:06:38.920
OK, so this was just part one
of this argument that we cannot

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:42.140
cover all of spacetime
with an inertial frame.

00:06:45.542 --> 00:06:47.000
So here's part two
of the argument.

00:06:50.750 --> 00:06:53.945
Suppose there was, in fact, a
very large region of space--

00:06:53.945 --> 00:06:55.820
now let's say it's near
the Earth's surface--

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.310
that could be covered by
a single Lorentz frame.

00:07:23.260 --> 00:07:23.780
OK?

00:07:23.780 --> 00:07:24.950
So I want you to
imagine that you're

00:07:24.950 --> 00:07:26.460
sending your beam of light up.

00:07:26.460 --> 00:07:28.335
And we're going to take
advantage of the fact

00:07:28.335 --> 00:07:29.870
that light is wave like.

00:07:29.870 --> 00:07:31.430
So what I want
you to do is think

00:07:31.430 --> 00:07:36.110
of the spacetime trajectory of
successive crests of this wave

00:07:36.110 --> 00:07:38.470
as it climbs out of the
gravitational potential.

00:07:58.163 --> 00:08:00.330
So I"m going to make my
spacetime diagram the way we

00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:04.670
like to do it with
time running up.

00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:08.400
And so this direction
represents height.

00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:10.770
So down here is the
bottom of the tower.

00:08:10.770 --> 00:08:12.592
So let's just make
the drawing clearer.

00:08:12.592 --> 00:08:14.550
Let's let this tick be
the bottom of the tower.

00:08:19.210 --> 00:08:20.710
This tick over here
will be the top.

00:08:26.030 --> 00:08:27.860
Now if we were just
in special relativity,

00:08:27.860 --> 00:08:30.318
there was no gravity, we know
light would just move on a 45

00:08:30.318 --> 00:08:33.179
degree angle on this thing.

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:36.270
We don't know yet what gravity
is going to do to this light.

00:08:36.270 --> 00:08:36.770
OK?

00:08:36.770 --> 00:08:38.900
But you can imagine that
whatever it's going to do,

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:42.260
it's going to bend it away in
some way from the trajectory

00:08:42.260 --> 00:08:44.510
that special relativity
would predict.

00:08:44.510 --> 00:08:49.930
So let's just imagine that
crest one of this light,

00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:52.220
it follows some
trajectory in spacetime

00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:53.510
that maybe looks like this.

00:08:57.740 --> 00:09:02.420
So here is the world
line of crest one.

00:09:09.510 --> 00:09:12.720
So what about the world
line of credit two?

00:09:19.480 --> 00:09:21.730
So let's think about what
the world line of credit two

00:09:21.730 --> 00:09:25.690
must be under this assumption
that we can, in fact, cover

00:09:25.690 --> 00:09:28.123
all of spacetime with
a single Lorentz frame.

00:09:28.123 --> 00:09:28.810
OK?

00:09:28.810 --> 00:09:49.390
If that is the case,
so if that is the case,

00:09:49.390 --> 00:09:52.550
no position and no
moment is special.

00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:53.050
OK?

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:55.150
Everything is actually
translation invariant

00:09:55.150 --> 00:09:56.350
in both time and space.

00:10:25.490 --> 00:10:27.300
So the second crest
is going to be

00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:30.720
emitted one wave period later.

00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:33.690
But there's absolutely nothing
special about spacetime one

00:10:33.690 --> 00:10:34.700
wave period later.

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:37.270
And as it moves
along, there can't

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:38.700
be anything special about this.

00:10:38.700 --> 00:10:42.060
If it is to be a global
Lorentz frame, whatever

00:10:42.060 --> 00:10:45.630
the trajectory is that the crest
two follows through spacetime,

00:10:45.630 --> 00:10:48.900
it's got to be congruent with
the trajectory of crest one.

00:10:48.900 --> 00:10:51.210
I've got to be able to
just simply slide them

00:10:51.210 --> 00:10:52.487
on top of each other.

00:10:52.487 --> 00:10:53.710
OK?

00:10:53.710 --> 00:10:55.665
That is what this
assumption demands.

00:11:11.280 --> 00:11:19.580
So this is going to look
something like this.

00:11:19.580 --> 00:11:20.290
OK?

00:11:20.290 --> 00:11:21.790
Artwork a little bit off.

00:11:21.790 --> 00:11:23.500
The key thing which
I want to emphasize,

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:29.780
though, is that if
this guy is congruent,

00:11:29.780 --> 00:11:32.850
the spacing between crest one
and crest two at the bottom,

00:11:32.850 --> 00:11:37.220
let's call it delta tb, there'll
be some spacing between the two

00:11:37.220 --> 00:11:37.820
at the top.

00:11:37.820 --> 00:11:38.780
We'll call it delta tt.

00:11:42.093 --> 00:11:43.010
They must be the same.

00:12:05.660 --> 00:12:06.670
But that's [INAUDIBLE].

00:12:06.670 --> 00:12:08.750
That is just a
period of the wave.

00:12:08.750 --> 00:12:10.460
And that's just up
to a factor of 2 pi.

00:12:10.460 --> 00:12:12.574
That's 1 over the frequency.

00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:28.550
So this implies delta tb is not
equal to delta t at the top.

00:12:28.550 --> 00:12:31.220
So a frequency at
the top is smaller.

00:12:31.220 --> 00:12:35.000
So the period will actually
be a little bit larger.

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:38.030
So when you think about
this argument carefully,

00:12:38.030 --> 00:12:40.790
the weak point is
this assumption

00:12:40.790 --> 00:12:43.270
that I can actually cover the
region with a large Lorentz

00:12:43.270 --> 00:12:43.770
frame.

00:12:43.770 --> 00:12:48.340
Remember what this is telling
me is that, essentially, there

00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:50.840
is no special direction, right?

00:12:50.840 --> 00:12:53.030
I can do translation,
variance in time and space,

00:12:53.030 --> 00:12:54.710
and they're all the same.

00:12:54.710 --> 00:12:57.330
But that's actually completely
contradicted by common sense.

00:12:57.330 --> 00:13:00.980
If there were no special
direction, why did it go down?

00:13:00.980 --> 00:13:03.550
There's obviously something
special about down, right?

00:13:11.670 --> 00:13:16.740
So we conclude we cannot have
a global Lorentz frame when

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:17.520
we've got gravity.

00:13:29.420 --> 00:13:33.120
And in case you want to read
a little bit more about it,

00:13:33.120 --> 00:13:35.780
I'll just give a highlight that
this argument was originally

00:13:35.780 --> 00:13:45.045
developed by a gentleman
named Alfred Shield.

00:13:55.870 --> 00:14:04.280
So that's unfortunate,
OK, from sort

00:14:04.280 --> 00:14:07.520
of a philosophical
perspective because the fact

00:14:07.520 --> 00:14:13.070
that we don't have a global
Lorentz frame makes you think,

00:14:13.070 --> 00:14:13.670
oh, crap.

00:14:13.670 --> 00:14:15.680
What are we going to do
with that framework we

00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:17.320
spent all this time developing?

00:14:17.320 --> 00:14:18.630
OK?

00:14:18.630 --> 00:14:22.160
The existence of a Lorentz frame
and many of the mathematics

00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:25.430
we've been developing for
the past few lectures,

00:14:25.430 --> 00:14:28.640
they all center around things
you can do in Lorentz frames.

00:14:28.640 --> 00:14:33.540
So it's kind of like, OK, so
do we just throw all that out?

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:39.450
Well, here is where Einstein's
key physical insight

00:14:39.450 --> 00:14:43.290
came in and gave us
the physical tools

00:14:43.290 --> 00:14:46.260
that then needed to be coupled
to some mathematics in order

00:14:46.260 --> 00:14:48.730
to turn it into something
that can be worked with

00:14:48.730 --> 00:14:50.610
but, nonetheless,
really save the day.

00:15:00.540 --> 00:15:03.660
So the key insight has
there's a few steps in it.

00:15:03.660 --> 00:15:07.588
So first thing, I was very
careful to use the word global

00:15:07.588 --> 00:15:09.630
when I ruled out the
existence of Lorentz frames.

00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:23.890
But I'm allowed to have
local Lorentz frames.

00:15:23.890 --> 00:15:24.390
Let's see.

00:15:24.390 --> 00:15:25.650
What does that actually mean?

00:15:35.820 --> 00:15:40.220
So I'll remind that a Lorentz
frame is a tool that we use

00:15:40.220 --> 00:15:42.270
to describe inertial observers.

00:15:42.270 --> 00:15:46.008
In fact, we often call
them inertial frames

00:15:46.008 --> 00:15:48.050
because they're sort of
the constant coordinates.

00:15:48.050 --> 00:15:50.480
They represent the coordinates
of an inertial observer

00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:53.965
who happens to be at rest in
that Lorentz coordinate system.

00:15:53.965 --> 00:15:54.840
So let's switch over.

00:15:54.840 --> 00:15:56.750
Let's start calling them
inertial frames for just

00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:57.290
a moment.

00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:17.150
So an inertial frame means that
there is nothing accelerating,

00:16:17.150 --> 00:16:24.010
so no accelerations on
observers or objects at rest

00:16:24.010 --> 00:16:24.670
in that frame.

00:16:31.750 --> 00:16:33.350
In other words, no
forces are acting.

00:16:44.790 --> 00:16:49.770
Einstein's insight
was to recognize

00:16:49.770 --> 00:16:56.330
that the next best thing
is a freely falling frame.

00:17:15.674 --> 00:17:16.670
OK?

00:17:16.670 --> 00:17:23.395
If you are in a freely falling
frame, to you, it sure as hell

00:17:23.395 --> 00:17:25.020
seems like there's
a force acting on it

00:17:25.020 --> 00:17:27.880
and there's some
accelerations acting upon it.

00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:30.750
But let's imagine you're in
this freely falling frame.

00:17:30.750 --> 00:17:34.320
And you have a bunch
of small objects

00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:35.748
that you release near you.

00:17:35.748 --> 00:17:37.831
Let's see if I can find
some bits of broken chalk.

00:17:42.545 --> 00:17:44.420
So when you're in this
really falling frame--

00:17:48.172 --> 00:17:49.880
this was a lot easier
when I was younger.

00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:52.460
All right, when you're in
this really falling frame, OK,

00:17:52.460 --> 00:17:55.500
and these objects
are all falling,

00:17:55.500 --> 00:18:02.360
there is no acceleration of
these objects relative to you.

00:18:02.360 --> 00:18:05.810
The reason for this is that
the gravitational force

00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:08.630
is proportional to the mass.

00:18:08.630 --> 00:18:18.830
And so the fact that
we have f equals ma.

00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:26.670
And fg proportional
to mass means

00:18:26.670 --> 00:18:33.665
that all objects in that
freely falling frame--

00:18:33.665 --> 00:18:35.790
this is a term that I'm
going to start using a lot.

00:18:40.550 --> 00:18:44.538
So I'm just going to
abbreviate it FFF.

00:18:44.538 --> 00:18:46.580
If I get really lazy, I
might call it an F cubed.

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:50.480
Anyway, l objects that are
in that freely falling frame,

00:18:50.480 --> 00:18:52.850
they're experiencing
the same acceleration.

00:18:52.850 --> 00:18:59.950
And so they experience
0 relative acceleration

00:18:59.950 --> 00:19:02.757
at least in the absence
of other forces, OK?

00:19:02.757 --> 00:19:04.090
Perhaps one of them is charging.

00:19:04.090 --> 00:19:05.800
There's an electric force.

00:19:05.800 --> 00:19:08.770
Well, then it sort of suggests
that the interesting force

00:19:08.770 --> 00:19:14.290
is the extra force provided
to that relative to what

00:19:14.290 --> 00:19:17.170
we call the gravitational force
that is driving this freefall.

00:19:44.590 --> 00:19:51.233
So I urge you to start getting
comfortable with this idea

00:19:51.233 --> 00:19:53.900
because we're going to find this
to be-- so one thing, which I'm

00:19:53.900 --> 00:19:56.570
going to do in a
couple of minutes,

00:19:56.570 --> 00:20:02.300
is actually a little
calculation that shows me

00:20:02.300 --> 00:20:11.010
I can, in fact,
always find a Lorentz

00:20:11.010 --> 00:20:14.426
frame in the vicinity of
any point in spacetime.

00:20:14.426 --> 00:20:15.100
OK?

00:20:15.100 --> 00:20:17.970
And so we're going to actually
regard that Lorentz frame

00:20:17.970 --> 00:20:21.120
as being the preferred
coordinate system of a freely

00:20:21.120 --> 00:20:23.490
falling observer, one
who is not accelerated

00:20:23.490 --> 00:20:26.460
relative to freefall
at that point.

00:20:26.460 --> 00:20:27.930
We are not in
freefall right now.

00:20:27.930 --> 00:20:30.090
The damn floor is pushing
us out of the way.

00:20:30.090 --> 00:20:33.540
But in this way of
doing things, we

00:20:33.540 --> 00:20:36.730
would actually regard us as
being the complicated people,

00:20:36.730 --> 00:20:37.380
OK?

00:20:37.380 --> 00:20:39.900
Someone who is merrily
plummeting to their death,

00:20:39.900 --> 00:20:41.650
they're actually the
simple observers,

00:20:41.650 --> 00:20:44.340
who are doing what they should
be doing, in some sense.

00:20:47.730 --> 00:20:51.670
So the key thing, a
way of saying this,

00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:53.700
so coming back to this
and just one more point

00:20:53.700 --> 00:20:57.840
about that, because
there are no relative

00:20:57.840 --> 00:21:06.830
accelerations, within
this frame, objects

00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:10.040
maintain their
relative velocities.

00:21:20.670 --> 00:21:22.567
That's basically the
definition of something

00:21:22.567 --> 00:21:23.400
that is an inertial.

00:21:23.400 --> 00:21:26.400
If I have a frame
where everything is--

00:21:26.400 --> 00:21:28.697
two objects are moving with
respect to each other at 1

00:21:28.697 --> 00:21:30.780
meter per second, they're
always moving at 1 meter

00:21:30.780 --> 00:21:33.090
per second, that's inertial.

00:21:33.090 --> 00:21:35.700
And so this sort of demands that
we do all of our experiments

00:21:35.700 --> 00:21:38.385
in plummeting elevators
or in space, right?

00:21:38.385 --> 00:21:39.760
OK, obviously,
you can't do that.

00:21:39.760 --> 00:21:41.218
So there's some
complications we're

00:21:41.218 --> 00:21:43.733
going to have to learn
the math to describe.

00:21:43.733 --> 00:21:45.900
But this is the way we're
going to from now on think

00:21:45.900 --> 00:21:48.810
about things is that the
freely falling frame is

00:21:48.810 --> 00:21:52.230
the most natural generalization
of an inertial frame

00:21:52.230 --> 00:21:55.980
that we describe using
Lorentz coordinates.

00:21:55.980 --> 00:21:59.550
Now before I discuss a
few details about this,

00:21:59.550 --> 00:22:01.410
an important thing
that is worth noting

00:22:01.410 --> 00:22:05.880
is that a very important
aspect of any realistic source

00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:09.794
of gravity is that
it is not uniform.

00:22:09.794 --> 00:22:10.650
OK?

00:22:10.650 --> 00:22:14.490
Gravity here is a
little bit stronger

00:22:14.490 --> 00:22:16.710
than gravity on the ceiling, OK?

00:22:16.710 --> 00:22:21.560
And it's a lot stronger than
gravity in geostationary orbit.

00:22:21.560 --> 00:22:24.390
We call this variation
in gravity tides.

00:22:29.370 --> 00:22:38.910
So tides break down the notion
of uniform freely falling

00:22:38.910 --> 00:22:39.410
frames.

00:22:49.570 --> 00:22:52.780
What this is telling
us is that this idea,

00:22:52.780 --> 00:22:55.300
if I'm going to create
this inertial frame that

00:22:55.300 --> 00:22:57.860
is essentially a
freely falling frame,

00:22:57.860 --> 00:23:00.400
it will have to
be a finite size.

00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:03.010
Hence, it's local
and not global.

00:23:03.010 --> 00:23:05.740
OK, physically,
this is telling me

00:23:05.740 --> 00:23:12.840
that, if I have a really
tall freely falling elevator,

00:23:12.840 --> 00:23:22.140
and I'm here, I have one friend
here and one friend down there,

00:23:22.140 --> 00:23:25.137
even if we start absolutely at
rest, let's say we're at rest.

00:23:25.137 --> 00:23:27.470
We measure reference back to
the walls of this elevator.

00:23:27.470 --> 00:23:29.550
It's a very stiff elevator.

00:23:29.550 --> 00:23:31.650
We will see the three
of us diverge away

00:23:31.650 --> 00:23:33.360
from each other with time, OK?

00:23:33.360 --> 00:23:35.820
Because this person, let's
say earth is down here,

00:23:35.820 --> 00:23:37.920
this person is feeling the--

00:23:37.920 --> 00:23:41.460
and using Newtonian intuition,
gravity is a little stronger.

00:23:41.460 --> 00:23:43.200
Gravity is medium.

00:23:43.200 --> 00:23:44.520
Gravity is weak.

00:23:44.520 --> 00:23:47.130
And so as viewed in that
freely falling frame,

00:23:47.130 --> 00:23:49.983
let's say we center it
on me here in the middle,

00:23:49.983 --> 00:23:52.650
I will see the person in the top
go up, the person at the bottom

00:23:52.650 --> 00:23:53.150
go down.

00:23:55.580 --> 00:24:01.330
Another way of
saying this, so let

00:24:01.330 --> 00:24:05.800
me just say that, so
a very tall elevator,

00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:13.420
we'll see a
separation of freefall

00:24:13.420 --> 00:24:14.830
since gravity is not uniform.

00:24:28.720 --> 00:24:32.770
But there's another
way of saying this.

00:24:32.770 --> 00:24:35.160
And what this is
telling me is imagine

00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:40.710
I made a spacetime diagram that
shows trajectories of the three

00:24:40.710 --> 00:24:45.550
of us, so the three of
us that are plummeting

00:24:45.550 --> 00:24:46.690
in this elevator, OK?

00:24:57.800 --> 00:24:59.690
What we find, if we
make our trajectories

00:24:59.690 --> 00:25:01.773
as we fall-- in fact, let's
just go ahead and make

00:25:01.773 --> 00:25:03.950
a little sketch of this.

00:25:03.950 --> 00:25:07.550
OK, so let's say
here is the middle.

00:25:10.330 --> 00:25:11.488
Here is the top.

00:25:11.488 --> 00:25:12.280
Here is the bottom.

00:25:12.280 --> 00:25:16.750
I'm going to draw this in
coordinates that are fixed

00:25:16.750 --> 00:25:19.060
on the person in the middle.

00:25:19.060 --> 00:25:22.660
So the person the middle, in
their freely falling frame,

00:25:22.660 --> 00:25:25.870
they think they're
standing still.

00:25:25.870 --> 00:25:29.330
They see the person at the
top moving up and away,

00:25:29.330 --> 00:25:33.308
the person at the bottom
moving up and away.

00:25:33.308 --> 00:25:36.900
It's a very similar story to
the little parable I sketched

00:25:36.900 --> 00:25:38.430
of that light pole moving up.

00:25:38.430 --> 00:25:41.098
These are not
congruent trajectories.

00:25:51.140 --> 00:25:54.440
Another way to say this is
that, in any moment, if I think

00:25:54.440 --> 00:25:58.280
of these as world lines,
I can, at any moment

00:25:58.280 --> 00:26:01.400
along the world line, I can
draw its tangent vector.

00:26:05.960 --> 00:26:11.715
The tangents do not
remain parallel.

00:26:16.420 --> 00:26:21.397
Now I'm going to take
you back to probably,

00:26:21.397 --> 00:26:23.230
I don't know when you
guys all learned this,

00:26:23.230 --> 00:26:25.355
but when you first started
learning about geometry.

00:26:25.355 --> 00:26:26.800
For me, it was in middle school.

00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:29.070
And when you first started
learning about geometry,

00:26:29.070 --> 00:26:31.150
you were usually doing
geometry on the plane.

00:26:31.150 --> 00:26:34.690
And they gave you various axioms
about the way things behaved.

00:26:34.690 --> 00:26:37.780
One of them is now known as
Euclid's parallelism axiom.

00:26:48.730 --> 00:26:52.780
And it states that if I have
two lines that start parallel,

00:26:52.780 --> 00:26:54.100
they remain parallel.

00:27:11.470 --> 00:27:13.700
If you dig into the
history of mathematics,

00:27:13.700 --> 00:27:19.400
this axiom bugged the crap out
of people for many, many years,

00:27:19.400 --> 00:27:20.300
OK?

00:27:20.300 --> 00:27:24.110
Because when you look at
pictures on a piece of paper

00:27:24.110 --> 00:27:27.900
or on a chalkboard or something
like that, it seems right, OK?

00:27:27.900 --> 00:27:30.770
But it really can't be
justified quite as rigorously

00:27:30.770 --> 00:27:33.380
as many other axioms
that Euclid wrote down.

00:27:33.380 --> 00:27:35.950
And it turns out, there's
an underlying assumption.

00:27:35.950 --> 00:27:39.200
The assumption is that
you are drawing your lines

00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:40.850
on a flat manifold.

00:27:57.130 --> 00:28:00.710
There's a ready counterexample.

00:28:00.710 --> 00:28:03.830
Go to the Earth's equator.

00:28:03.830 --> 00:28:06.440
You start, say,
somewhere in Brazil.

00:28:06.440 --> 00:28:08.420
Your friend starts
somewhere in Africa.

00:28:08.420 --> 00:28:12.440
Both of you stand on the
equator and go due north.

00:28:12.440 --> 00:28:15.500
You are moving on
parallel trajectories.

00:28:15.500 --> 00:28:18.760
You will intersect
at the North Pole.

00:28:18.760 --> 00:28:19.260
OK?

00:28:19.260 --> 00:28:19.890
Well, guess what?

00:28:19.890 --> 00:28:21.210
You ain't moving
on a flat manifold.

00:28:21.210 --> 00:28:22.918
You're moving on the
surface of a sphere.

00:28:22.918 --> 00:28:26.670
OK, curvature causes initially
parallel trajectories

00:28:26.670 --> 00:28:29.940
to become non-parallel.

00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:33.660
What this is telling us is that
the manifold I'm going to want

00:28:33.660 --> 00:28:39.300
to use to describe events when
I have gravity cannot be flat.

00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:41.940
I'm going to have to
introduce curvature into it.

00:28:41.940 --> 00:28:44.670
Take us a little while to unpack
precisely mathematically what

00:28:44.670 --> 00:28:46.210
that means.

00:28:46.210 --> 00:28:50.790
But this is sort of a sign that
things got more complicated.

00:28:50.790 --> 00:28:53.670
And tides are the way in
which that complication

00:28:53.670 --> 00:28:56.930
is being introduced.

00:28:56.930 --> 00:29:03.000
So switch pages here.

00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:22.340
So what we have basically danced
around and put together here

00:29:22.340 --> 00:29:25.520
is one formulation
of what is known

00:29:25.520 --> 00:29:29.765
as the principle of equivalence.

00:29:56.990 --> 00:30:00.620
The principle of equivalence,
or one formulation of it,

00:30:00.620 --> 00:30:23.420
tells me that over
sufficiently small regions,

00:30:23.420 --> 00:30:42.490
the motion of freely falling
particles due to gravity cannot

00:30:42.490 --> 00:30:50.099
be distinguished from
uniform acceleration.

00:30:55.843 --> 00:30:57.260
The physical
manifestation of this

00:30:57.260 --> 00:30:58.635
is that if you're
an observer who

00:30:58.635 --> 00:31:01.050
is in that freely falling
frame moving due to gravity,

00:31:01.050 --> 00:31:03.720
you are also experiencing
that uniform acceleration.

00:31:03.720 --> 00:31:06.650
So you see no net acceleration.

00:31:06.650 --> 00:31:08.090
This particular
formulation of it

00:31:08.090 --> 00:31:10.616
is known as the weak
equivalence principle.

00:31:16.928 --> 00:31:18.970
I'm going to give you a
couple variations on this

00:31:18.970 --> 00:31:21.880
in just a second.

00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:27.040
One thing that's
important about it is,

00:31:27.040 --> 00:31:32.750
essentially, it's a
statement that, if you

00:31:32.750 --> 00:31:38.100
think about Newton's laws,
the idea that f equals ma

00:31:38.100 --> 00:31:40.670
and the force of gravity
is proportional to m,

00:31:40.670 --> 00:31:43.460
it's a fairly precise
statement that you

00:31:43.460 --> 00:31:46.190
think of that m as the
gravitational charge.

00:31:46.190 --> 00:31:48.410
It's saying that the
gravitational charge,

00:31:48.410 --> 00:31:50.900
the gravitational mass
and the inertial mass

00:31:50.900 --> 00:31:52.610
are the same thing.

00:31:52.610 --> 00:31:54.923
That's actually a
testable statement.

00:31:54.923 --> 00:31:56.840
What you can do is look
at materials that have

00:31:56.840 --> 00:31:58.000
very different compositions.

00:31:58.000 --> 00:31:59.417
In particular,
what you want to do

00:31:59.417 --> 00:32:01.130
is look at things
that maybe have

00:32:01.130 --> 00:32:03.920
different ratios of
neutrons to protons

00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:07.730
or have highly bound nuclei
with lots of gluons in them

00:32:07.730 --> 00:32:09.260
or various kinds
of fields that you

00:32:09.260 --> 00:32:11.810
can imagine perhaps couple
to gravity differently

00:32:11.810 --> 00:32:14.040
than the quarks do.

00:32:14.040 --> 00:32:16.760
And so there are what are called
free fall experiments to test

00:32:16.760 --> 00:32:24.640
this, which really
basically just boils down

00:32:24.640 --> 00:32:27.290
to dropping lots of different
elements of the periodic table

00:32:27.290 --> 00:32:30.040
and making sure they all
fall at the same rate.

00:32:30.040 --> 00:32:34.910
And the answer is that they
fall at exactly the same rate

00:32:34.910 --> 00:32:36.670
within experimental precision.

00:32:36.670 --> 00:32:42.850
And the last time I looked
it up, well, what they do

00:32:42.850 --> 00:32:50.020
is they demonstrate the WEP,
the Weak Equivalence Principle,

00:32:50.020 --> 00:32:53.980
is valid to about, I believe,
it's about a part in 10

00:32:53.980 --> 00:32:54.700
to the minus 13.

00:32:54.700 --> 00:32:56.075
Might be a little
bit better now.

00:32:58.640 --> 00:33:03.600
So bear with me just
one second here.

00:33:09.530 --> 00:33:10.850
OK, so good.

00:33:10.850 --> 00:33:13.360
We've got this notion here.

00:33:13.360 --> 00:33:15.340
And you might now
think, OK, great.

00:33:15.340 --> 00:33:17.780
I have a way of
generalizing what

00:33:17.780 --> 00:33:19.890
the notion of an
inertial frame is.

00:33:19.890 --> 00:33:22.570
Is this enough for
me to move forward?

00:33:22.570 --> 00:33:34.350
Can we now do all of
physics by just applying

00:33:34.350 --> 00:33:42.900
the laws of special relativity
in freely falling frames

00:33:42.900 --> 00:33:45.660
or, putting it this way, our
new notion of an inertial frame?

00:33:54.560 --> 00:33:56.270
For two reasons that
are closely related,

00:33:56.270 --> 00:33:57.710
this doesn't quite work.

00:33:57.710 --> 00:34:04.377
And it comes down to the fact
that because of tides, we

00:34:04.377 --> 00:34:04.960
can't do that.

00:34:28.620 --> 00:34:31.250
What this basically means is
that the transformation that

00:34:31.250 --> 00:34:35.192
puts you into a freely falling
frame here is not the same

00:34:35.192 --> 00:34:36.650
as the transformation
that puts you

00:34:36.650 --> 00:34:39.500
into a freely falling frame
10,000 miles over the Earth's

00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:40.909
surface, OK?

00:34:40.909 --> 00:34:42.739
There are different
transformations

00:34:42.739 --> 00:34:45.320
at different locations
in spacetime.

00:34:45.320 --> 00:34:47.840
This comes down the idea that
it's not a global Lorentz

00:34:47.840 --> 00:34:48.380
frame, OK?

00:34:48.380 --> 00:34:51.230
We had a sequence of
local Lorentz frames

00:34:51.230 --> 00:34:52.850
that we have to link up.

00:35:16.808 --> 00:35:19.100
So I'm going to do a calculation
in just a moment where

00:35:19.100 --> 00:35:24.020
we explicitly show that we can
always go into a frame that

00:35:24.020 --> 00:35:29.120
is locally Lorentz, but that
there's a term that I'm going

00:35:29.120 --> 00:35:30.680
to very strongly
argue is essentially

00:35:30.680 --> 00:35:33.590
the curvature associated with
the spacetime metric that

00:35:33.590 --> 00:35:36.230
sets the size of what
that region actually is.

00:35:40.320 --> 00:35:43.940
So what we are
going to do, what is

00:35:43.940 --> 00:35:49.570
going to guide our physics
as we move forward is,

00:35:49.570 --> 00:35:53.080
essentially, we're going to take
advantage of a reformulation--

00:35:56.665 --> 00:36:05.047
there we go-- of the
equivalence principle, which

00:36:05.047 --> 00:36:06.255
I'm going to word as follows.

00:36:11.250 --> 00:36:25.160
In sufficiently small
regions of spacetime,

00:36:25.160 --> 00:36:37.470
we can find a representation or
a coordinate system such that--

00:36:37.470 --> 00:36:39.220
I don't want to cram
this into the margin.

00:36:39.220 --> 00:36:40.220
So I'll switch boards--

00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:13.930
the laws of physics reduce to
those of special relativity.

00:37:13.930 --> 00:37:19.390
This is known as the Einstein
equivalence principle.

00:37:19.390 --> 00:37:22.923
At least, that's the name that
Carroll uses in his textbook.

00:37:22.923 --> 00:37:24.340
A couple books use
different ones.

00:37:24.340 --> 00:37:26.215
But this is a very nice
one because it really

00:37:26.215 --> 00:37:30.700
is the principle by which
Einstein guided us to rewriting

00:37:30.700 --> 00:37:33.230
the laws of physics.

00:37:33.230 --> 00:37:35.830
So we've got a weak equivalence
principle, an Einstein

00:37:35.830 --> 00:37:37.030
equivalence principle.

00:37:37.030 --> 00:37:39.010
Just as an aside, there
is something called

00:37:39.010 --> 00:37:40.886
a strong equivalence principle.

00:37:49.125 --> 00:37:51.000
We're not going to talk
about this very much,

00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:53.625
but I'm going to give it to you
because it's just kind of cool.

00:37:56.950 --> 00:38:07.420
It tells me that gravity
falls in a gravitational field

00:38:07.420 --> 00:38:09.490
in a way that is
indistinguishable from mass.

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:24.730
That's a little weird.

00:38:24.730 --> 00:38:27.940
I'm not going to explain
it very much right now.

00:38:27.940 --> 00:38:29.770
A way to think about
it will become clearer

00:38:29.770 --> 00:38:31.870
in some future problem sets.

00:38:31.870 --> 00:38:33.910
Basically what it's
telling us is that when

00:38:33.910 --> 00:38:35.410
you make very strong--

00:38:35.410 --> 00:38:38.440
when you make any kind
of a bound object,

00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:40.930
some of the mass of that
object, in the sense

00:38:40.930 --> 00:38:43.750
of the mass that is
measured by orbits,

00:38:43.750 --> 00:38:46.690
can be thought of as
